  "prompt": "I'm a student of the IITs and my dream is to become a maths faculty member in IIT JEE coaching. As the pattern of IIT JEE is regularly changing, is it safe to become a faculty member in coachings of Kota or just prepare for a company?",
  "response": "Here's a balanced perspective on your career options:\n\nCoaching Faculty Pros:\n1. High paying job (\u20b95-15 lakhs per annum)\n2. Respected profession\n3. Satisfaction of teaching\n4. Continuous learning\n5. Flexible working hours\n6. Opportunity to inspire students\n\nCoaching Faculty Cons:\n1. Competitive market\n2. Regular syllabus updates\n3. High stress environment\n4. Less job security compared to corporate\n\nCorporate Job Pros:\n1. More stable career\n2. Better long-term financial growth\n3. Structured career progression\n4. Global exposure\n5. Multiple skill development\n\nCorporate Job Cons:\n1. Less passion-driven work\n2. Less teaching satisfaction\n3. Standard work environment\n\nRecommendations:\n1. Keep both options open\n2. Build strong mathematical skills\n3. Develop teaching capabilities\n4. Create digital content/tutorials\n5. Network with existing faculty members\n6. Stay updated with latest exam patterns\n\nBest approach:\n- Start with coaching\n- Simultaneously prepare corporate skills\n- Keep options flexible\n- Continuous skill enhancement\n\nYour passion and skills will ultimately determine your success.",
